   Privacy

                               PRIVACY POLICY

   The Fair Political Practices Commission does not collect information on
   any individual visitor to our Internet site unless the visitor chooses
   to make information available to us.
     * We do not place "cookies" on the computers of visitors to our site.
     * We may retain e-mail messages requesting assistance or commenting
       on our site so that we can respond to the sender and improve our
       service. Any information received is used for lawful purposes of
       the FPPC and is not distributed to anyone outside the FPPC except
       as required by law.
     * We may at times monitor the number of visitors to the different
       pages on our site, and keep track of the various types of web
       browsers used by our customers, so that we can make our site
       accessible to as many people as possible. Any information collected
       in this manner is used for lawful purposes of the FPPC and is not
       distributed to anyone outside the FPPC except as required by law.

                  Note on the California Public Records Act

   This policy does not limit public access to information required to be
   public by law. Generally speaking, most documents filed with the Fair
   Political Practices Commission are public records. For more information
   on Political Reform Act enforcement matters and the Public Records Act,
   click here.

                                 Contact Us

   If you have questions about our privacy policy or suggestions for
   improvement, click here or call 1-866-ASK-FPPC.

